cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on natural language processing (NLP) and named entity recognition (NER) using deep learning methods. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper uses Bidirectional Long Short-Term Memory (Bi-LSTM) and Conditional Random Field (CRF) for the deep learning model. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper discusses the use of Word2Vec and semantic feature vectors for NER. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a potential category as the paper uses neural networks for NER. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also possible as NER plays an important role in text-based information retrieval.
